title: Bank strike tomorrow: FBIOA launches protest against Narendra Modi govt's banking, labour reforms

organizations.name: fed of bank of india officer

text:
Sanjoy Das. (ANI) The Fed of Bank of India Officer’s Associations (FBIOA) have called a bank strike tomorrow for banks across India against the Narendra Modi -led government’s monetary policy and reforms in the banking industry and labour laws. Sanjoy Das the Vice President of FBIOA in an interview with the media said, “Under United Forum of Bank Unions’ banner we have called for all India bank strike tomorrow. We are compelled to call the strike. It is against government’s monetary policy and reforms in banking industry & labour law.”
Further details awaited.
